reviews.headline: Removed everything
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] It has a fresh scent that's not too loud. The texture is smooth and removes make up easily. Removes even that stubborn make-up

reviews.headline: Refreshing Cleansing Balm
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review. First time using a cleaning balm, won't be my last. Removed impurities and refreshed myself without feeling dried out or clogged. There are better comparable but this is great if you're looking for a new and affordable makeup remover. Thick and long lasting consistency.

reviews.headline: Irritates my skin
reviews.comments: I wanted to love this so much but it irritated my skin so bad. My forehead was so itchy that I thought I was going to need to get myself a straight jacket to keep myself from scratching.

reviews.headline: Love this!
reviews.comments: Thank you Garnier for coming out with this cleansing balm!  It works just the same if not better than the really expensive balms.  Save yourself some money and buy this brand.

reviews.headline: LOVE IT, BUY BUY BUY
reviews.comments: This product is amazing, it's the only makeup remover that completely removes waterproof mascara. My lashes feel absolute relief after using this cleansing balm, also needs a small amount for grand results!

reviews.headline: Happy Find!
reviews.comments: I loved this product and was happy to come across it! Make up wipes and micellar water dont work for me but this balm gets through coats of mascara easily and doesnt burn if it gets in my eyes a little lol. Always left with a fresh and clean feeling.

reviews.headline: DOES NOT REMOVE MAKEUP WELL
reviews.comments: I still had to use what was left over of my other makeup remover. And I don't actually wear that much makeup. So it's not like it has layers to go through

reviews.headline: Good stuff!
reviews.comments: I was using Neutrogena's makeup remover balm, which is great but costs the same tor half as much. This is just as good. In fact, better, because I need to use less than I did of the Neutrogena. No scent, which I love. Leaves my face clean and moisturized.

reviews.headline: I made the switch
reviews.comments: I love balms for makeup removal. They gently remove all your makeup without tugging or scrubbing. I just hate how expensive some of them are. This product is less than half the cost of the brands i was using. I was hoping these would be good, and they were. I'll continue to buy the Garnier brand over Clinque or Banila Co.

reviews.headline: Added Dyes
reviews.comments: Bought this product only to return immediately due to the dyes in the ingredients list. Dyes should NOT be in skincare products. As someone with sensitive eyes and vision problems as well, I do not feel safe putting this anywhere near my eyes. I hope Garnier removes the dyes and only then would I be interested in repurchasing.

reviews.headline: Not the best
reviews.comments: I was excited to try this, but wasn't a huge fan and will probably return. The texture is strange and it's supposed to be safe for eye makeup, however it makes my vision blurry.

reviews.headline: I was hoping I would like this and I did.
reviews.comments: I have been using another Makeup Removing Balm and It's really expensive and I thought I would give this a try and it's more than half the price and works great.  I will be buying this from now on.

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: I loved this product it took away all my makeup really fast and didn't break me out

reviews.headline: Best Cleansing Balm!
reviews.comments: I am so glad I tried this balm because it is hands down the best makeup removing cleanser I have ever used. I have very sensitive skin and this does NOT irritate my skin at all nor does it have any kind of smell, so I have no idea what the other reviewers are talking about. This stuff removes all of my long wear makeup, including all eye makeup, so there is no longer a need to use a separate liquid makeup remover.

reviews.headline: Works well but causes eye irritation
reviews.comments: This stuff is great at removing makeup, but causes eye irritation. After using it my eyes will burn and water for hours. I've never had this issue with any other cleansing balm.

reviews.headline: worst product
reviews.comments: the worst cleansing balm i have ever used if your skin in sencitive it will irttate it so bad and it burn my eyes never buy it agan instead buy the clean it zero balm that is way better

reviews.headline: Miracle Makeup Remover
reviews.comments: This product is amazing! I apply a nice amount and rub it into my face before applying water. It all comes off and it leaves your face feeling really soft and with this glow.

reviews.headline: Miracle Makeup Remover
reviews.comments: This product is amazing! I apply a nice amount and rub it into my face before applying water. It all comes off and it leaves your face feeling really soft and with this glow.

reviews.headline: Chemical
reviews.comments: The smell is insanely strong of chemicals and it irritated the skin around my eyes in a way that almost resembled chemical burns. I would say if you have sensitive skin STAY AWAY.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Review: Garnier Makeup Removing Cleansing Balm

The Garnier Makeup Removing Cleansing Balm has quickly become a staple in my skincare routine, and I can't wait to share my experience with this product. Designed to effortlessly melt away makeup, even stubborn waterproof formulas, this cleansing balm is an impressive option for anyone seeking effective yet gentle makeup removal.

Packaging:
The balm comes in a sturdy, travel-friendly jar that feels both practical and luxurious. The lid seals tightly, preventing any spills or messes, which is always a bonus for those of us who are constantly on the go.

Texture and Application:
Upon opening the jar, you are greeted with a rich, buttery balm that has a pleasant, subtle fragrance. The texture is smooth, and it feels incredibly soothing on the skin. A little goes a long way; I typically scoop out a small amount and rub it between my fingers to warm it up before applying it to my dry face. What I love most is how it starts to melt almost instantly upon contact with the skin, breaking down even the heaviest makeup with ease.

Effectiveness:
The cleansing power is outstanding. It effectively melted away my makeup, including foundation, mascara, and even long-wearing lip products, without the need for excessive rubbing. I appreciate that it does not leave an oily residue behind, which is often the case with some balms. Instead, my skin feels clean and refreshed after rinsing.

Skin Compatibility:
As someone with sensitive skin, I am always cautious about trying new products. I was pleased to find that the Garnier Cleansing Balm did not irritate my skin; in fact, it felt very soothing. The formulation, loaded with nourishing ingredients like coconut oil and shea butter, left my skin feeling moisturized without any heaviness or clogging of pores.

Final Thoughts:
Overall, the Garnier Makeup Removing Cleansing Balm exceeds my expectations in terms of performance and skin compatibility. It provides a luxurious cleansing experience at an affordable price point, making it accessible for all. If you are looking for an effective way to remove makeup without the harshness of wipes or foams, I highly recommend giving this cleansing balm a try.

Pros: Effective makeup removal, gentle on the skin, nourishing ingredients, pleasant texture
Cons: Jar packaging may not be the most hygienic option for some users

In conclusion, Garnier has crafted a fantastic product that embodies both efficacy and care, ensuring that my skin remains happy and healthy.
faceoff_positive.headline: Love this stuff

faceoff_negative.comments:
Erase It All Makeup Cleansing Balm: This cleansing balm has been formulated with Hyaluronic Acid to cleanse & gently remove all types of longwear makeup: eye, lips, face & sunscreen residue. Use as a morning face cleanser & a makeup remover in the evening
Cleanses With 24H Hydration: Thanks to its formula powered by Hyaluronic Acid, our cleansing balm makeup remover leaves skin looking plumper instantly and over time. This facial cleanser leaves skin hydrated for 24H with non-greasy finish
For Best Use: To remove makeup & cleanse skin, massage a generous amount of cleansing balm into dry skin using circular motions. Add water to create a milky lather & rinse clean with warm water. Use as a face mask by applying to clean skin for 10 minutes
Garnier Commits to Greener Beauty: Garnier is approved by Cruelty Free International. This makeup remover balm is free of fragrance, sulfates and silicones and is non-comedogenic and won't clog pores
Garnier carries an array of products for your hair and skin care needs, from shampoos, color care and styling products to formulas that cleanse, moisturize and help protect your skin
